.TH SPEC 1 "2026" "The-JLC-Project" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
spec \- print file contents suppressing adjacent duplicate lines
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B spec
.I file
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B spec
reads
.I file
and writes each line to standard output, skipping any line that is identical
to the immediately preceding line.
Non-adjacent duplicate lines are
.B not
suppressed.
This is the JLC equivalent of
.BR uniq (1).
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
Success.
.TP
.B 1
Wrong number of arguments.
.TP
.B 2
Cannot open file.
.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
Remove adjacent duplicate lines:
.EX
spec data.txt
.EE
.TP
Combined with srt to remove all duplicates:
.EX
srt file.txt | spec
.EE
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR uniq (1),
.BR srt (1)
.SH AUTHORS
The-JLC-Project contributors.
